"subjects":[{"id":".NET/C#","path":"/subject/.NET%2FC%23/","title":".NET/C#"},{"id":"NinjaTrader","path":"/subject/NinjaTrader/","title":"NinjaTrader"},{"id":"DirectX","path":"/subject/DirectX/","title":"DirectX"}]}},{"node":{"title":"Multi-Threading Consideration for NinjaScript - NinjaTrader 8 Help Guide","path":"/content/work/multi-threading-consideration-for-ninja-script-ninj/","date":"June 2016","timeToRead":1,"description":"NinjaScript was event-driven and multi-threaded, which meant that 3rd party C# developers needed to be aware of how to handle programming scenarios that sometimes needed to be dispatched between parallel threads.","content":"\n","cover_image":"/work/images/multi.png","company":"NinjaTrader LLC","tags":[{"id":"Technical writing","path":"/tag/Technical%20writing/","title":"Technical writing"}],"subjects":[{"id":".NET/C#","path":"/subject/.NET%2FC%23/","title":".NET/C#"},{"id":"Multi-threaded programming","path":"/subject/Multi-threaded%20programming/","title":"Multi-threaded programming"},{"id":"NinjaTrader","path":"/subject/NinjaTrader/","title":"NinjaTrader"}]}},{"node":{"title":"Share Service - NinjaTrader 8 Help Guide","path":"/content/work/share-service-ninja-trader-8-help-guide/","date":"June 2016","timeToRead":1,"description":"NinjaTrader version 8 introduced a new class of objects that could be used to communicate to 3rd party APIs like Twitter, Facebook, or custom made to meet customer use cases. This was the API Reference that enabled a developer to start using this group of methods and types.","content":"<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 1554 966' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-dc5a4cb1d105493fcce2780d66ff8eea'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-dc5a4cb1d105493fcce2780d66ff8ee