\" alt=\"alt text\"></noscript></p>\n","cover_image":"/work/images/share1.png","company":"NinjaTrader LLC","tags":[{"id":"Technical writing","path":"/tag/Technical%20writing/","title":"Technical writing"}],"subjects":[{"id":".NET/C#","path":"/subject/.NET%2FC%23/","title":".NET/C#"},{"id":"NinjaTrader","path":"/subject/NinjaTrader/","title":"NinjaTrader"}]}},{"node":{"title":"Software Product Management - NinjaTrader 8 Beta and Major Release","path":"/content/work/software-product-management-ninja-trader-8-beta-and/","date":"June 2016","timeToRead":1,"description":"I was promoted to Product Manager after working as a technical support lead for the NinjaTrader platform. When I was promoted, much of the early planning and specification was already completed, so I was brought on to help with the engineering implementation, user acceptance testing, and documentation up until the first major release of NinjaTrader 8 in November of 2016.","content":"<ul>\n<li>I was Junior Product Manager.</li>\n<li>Responsible for updating legacy documentation, comparing to current programming interfaces, and conducting code reviews to understand changes to new technology.</li>\n<li>Inherited project from the former product manager who had developed much of the legacy documentation and set standards for writing styles.</li>\n<li>Worked in efforts to fill in gaps where needed between custom requests and existing API code that could be exposed.</li>\n<li>Met routinely with developers to help understand expected code functionality and develop reasonable API behaviors and errors that would foster an \"exploratory\" environment.</li>\n<li>Fundamentally changed many-core events, GUI framework, and exposed low-level accessibility to fulfill change requests between major release cycles.</li>\n<li>Rehashed user experiences working with customer-facing teams, company stakeholders, and key partners to help ensure the milestone transition between products was seamless.</li>\n<li>Painstakingly reviewed implementations and changes with quality to teams to ensure consistency between naming, color, and sub-class behaviors.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 1541 912' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-3947419781788c87cfc48cebb04470a0'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-3947419781788c87cfc48cebb04470a0)' width='1541' height='912' xlink:href='data:image/png%3bbase64%2ciVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAEAAAAAmCAIAAAD7pgrOAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAJVUlEQVRYw81Za3AT1xXmd7FlbINtjGU99iGt3pItY/yiQEsdAgGa0ACZJp02MyUkM2nJDAHyI50ApZRpJsSAHWeIYUhCKM%2bAKaRD02GamfIIxiBswCbGxlhgS7Keu1ppV6LfasF2h4KDILhHx1d37z337Pn2nsddeRwbY%2b9ylEPLScxJHOUkig3zsGSKo0KUF2Oxe8wLPB/neTHFAi/eEcEYl8QEfkhmWD4lGUugE5OV33%2bL0Zlnx91Jl0LBUP/tfs%2bAx%2b/3ez3egD/Asuzg4KB/0B8Oha9evupyufr7%2bzmWw2UgEEAbDAYlAb8fbTAg9bHc5/MJcSE9G5LJZPoAIpEI7PN4PTDL45FamOJ2u2/evDkwMHD9%2bvX29nZcYmogRbAVl319fV6vVwIQDAIJlkAgGo2OAYD7CXhgPay8lSJYBltv3LiBFlMwvbe3Fy0c80H2PG0AWP%2bQqQfPJp/UI3s0ALhtVEwG48l%2bPhEUkugH4smIkETA%2bvhEH5dAP6X0fyAciSeRTPBiJCqEYwkuKobjCUQzG4h5/LHbESHwSABEUfy%2bABKpux9zx%2bqv8Rva2PWXuMM3Y5va2Q1t3MmBeOO16JoL7N/dsSHJBzwCaS4U93zRufbAd5uO9TTs6Vx30fuPS76T/7r1RXN33Yneph8KgGxVHytc8kRaB4Wz3vi/%2b6Muv/BNP/%2bthz/njZ10c51hcVT/SCbueEO3rgVa%2biId1wLnrvlbrnrPBmL93YPtrlvfXA%2b1Jh/FwR4FQMoBQn5/24XWy67WkM/T09nRfuF815W2S%2bfPdXVcbjv/bZxjR9WAaHZddF2%2bdNU7MNjT1Xu5raPlbOv1ru4b3b2tLa7OK99duXLlIaGVPgCZBFFkOc436OeifJSPeX2%2bcCQSCIUCwaDXNxiPx0fXIAjIQqgELMeGUBoiYd%2bgLxQOC6IQDocCAT%2bKyRMDAEWJRAIt5BIpGhmLcmfk5ZDAUH%2bkpKwBqkbNWkPL5SXpA8DD6O7uRklCGUI6l0uSnOlRg5Dp5ZSPQdQjCCDHy%2bkfnZ6eHozwPB8Oh9FH5cIgprBcrnruFMmDWHX79m0oQSv3QSgaWAjlUJL%2bDkBCSJFcj3pTBD%2bWkfS5%2b9y33EP3RguDMAV5eaH8CNEJhUJyIQOSoUqHESyH26BKAwvGZdPlWeiHT47cyfRjACpgAc4O/hRFUhQKhiMhlotEI3DksHTagXNDDP37b4mnGEgRTg0QwA